  <refnamediv>
    <refname>distfun_unifstat</refname>
    <refpurpose>Uniform  mean and variance</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   M = distfun_unifstat ( a , b )
   [M,V] = distfun_unifstat ( a , b )
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>a :</term>
      <listitem><para> a matrix of doubles, the lower bound</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>b :</term>
      <listitem><para> a matrix of doubles, the upper bound (with a&lt;=b)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>M :</term>
      <listitem><para> a matrix of doubles, the mean</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>V :</term>
      <listitem><para> a matrix of doubles, the variance</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Computes statistics from the Uniform distribution.
   </para>
   <para>
The mean and variance of the Uniform distribution are
   </para>
   <para>
<latex>
\begin{eqnarray}
M &amp;=&amp; \frac{a+b}{2} \\
V &amp;=&amp; \frac{(b-a)^2}{12}
\end{eqnarray}
</latex>
   </para>
   <para>
Any scalar input argument is expanded to a matrix of
doubles of the same size as the other input arguments.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[

a = 1:6;
b = 2:7;
[M,V] = distfun_unifstat ( a , b )
me = [1.5    2.5    3.5    4.5    5.5    6.5];
ve = [0.0833333    0.0833333    0.0833333    0.0833333    0.0833333    0.0833333];

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

